messages.message: we can extend the doc widget to take manual annotations so an operator can tell us the location of the data, and yes an input field showing next to the data in the doc widget would be nice… @Travis @Youssef let’s see if we can build something like this in the nest few release… :slightly_smiling_face:

thanks for sharing this @Anant, this was an interesting demo. Couple things that stood out to me —
• Their UX for work queue (https://youtu.be/OIzjmNoV37Q?t=111) and human review was pretty neat.  [Glad we are moving in that direction already :slightly_smiling_face: ]
• The input is not very hard but the end to end business solution using integration with uipath makes it pretty powerful. [Have we considered such partnerships with UIPath like them? Like IB being the extraction partner for an end to end RPA cust of UiPath.]
